This works but is tricky to install. You need to extract the files from the CD1 iso and make a new iso out of these files. Then load with DAEMON tools, and simply change mounted image when the install asks for cd change.
Alternatively, you can extract the CD1 iso and burn the files on a cd, and burn the other to images on cds also, and install it from three cds as it is meant to be done.
